OL,3,C'Abandoned': Aid organisations sound
OL,4,Calarm as Sudan war enters fourth year
OL,6,FThe conflict in Sudan has entered its
OL,7,Ffourth year, with aid groups and the
OL,8,Fgovernment lamenting the lack of
OL,9,Fattention the war gets, despite the
OL,10,Frampant massacres, famine, and dire
OL,11,Fsituation facing civilians.
OL,13,FOver 13 million people have fled their
OL,14,Fhomes since the conflict erupted, with
OL,15,Fno end in sight as the fighting
OL,16,Fbetween the official military and the
OL,17,Fparamilitary Rapid Support Forces
OL,18,F(RSF) continues.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30502
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1776255070
OL,3,C'Abandoned': Aid organisations sound
OL,4,Calarm as Sudan war enters fourth year
OL,6,FGrowing evidence shows regional powers
OL,7,Flike the United Arab Emirates backing
OL,8,Fcombatants behind the scenes.
OL,10,FAttempts by the United States and
OL,11,Fregional powers, now distracted by the
OL,12,FIran war, have failed to establish a
OL,13,Fceasefire.
OL,15,F"This grim and chastening anniversary
OL,16,Fmarks another year when the world has
OL,17,Ffailed to meet the test of Sudan,"
OL,18,FUnited Nations humanitarian chief Tom
OL,19,FFletcher said.
OL,26,@wD@AOUyD@bO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
