OL,3,C'Abandoned': Aid organisations sound
OL,4,Calarm as Sudan war enters fourth year
OL,6,FThe war has pushed parts of Sudan into
OL,7,Ffamine. The number of people with
OL,8,Fsevere acute malnutrition, the most
OL,9,Fdangerous and deadly kind, is expected
OL,10,Fto increase to 800,000, the Integrated
OL,11,FFood Security Phase Classification,
OL,12,Fsaid in February.
OL,14,FAbout 34 million people, or almost two
OL,15,Fof every three Sudanese, need
OL,16,Fassistance, the UN says. Only 63% of
OL,17,Fhealth facilities remain fully or
OL,18,Fpartially functional amid disease
OL,19,Foutbreaks, including cholera,
OL,20,Faccording to the World Health
OL,21,FOrganization.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
