OL,3,C'Abandoned': Aid organisations sound
OL,4,Calarm as Sudan war enters fourth year
OL,6,FThe tensions sparked between military
OL,7,Fchief Gen. Abdel-Fattah Burhan, who
OL,8,Fchairs the ruling sovereign council,
OL,9,Fand RSF commander Gen. Mohamed Hamdan
OL,10,FDagalo, who was Burhan's deputy there.
OL,12,FSudan is now essentially divided
OL,13,Fbetween a military-backed,
OL,14,Finternationally recognised government
OL,15,Fin the capital, Khartoum, and a rival
OL,16,FRSF-controlled administration in
OL,17,FDarfur.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30509
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1776255070
OL,3,C'Abandoned': Aid organisations sound
OL,4,Calarm as Sudan war enters fourth year
OL,6,FThe military has established control
OL,7,Fover the north, east and central
OL,8,Fregions, including Sudan's Red Sea
OL,9,Fports and its oil refineries and
OL,10,Fpipelines. The RSF and allies control
OL,11,FDarfur and areas in the Kordofan
OL,12,Fregion along the border with South
OL,13,FSudan. Both regions include many of
OL,14,FSudan's oil fields and gold mines.
OL,16,FWhile Egypt supports Sudan's military,
OL,17,Fthe UAE and Ethiopia are accused by UN
OL,18,Fexperts and rights groups of providing
OL,19,Farms to the RSF. The UAE has rejected
OL,20,Fthe accusation.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
